examples.en: The band feels ready for new challenges.
The new lawsuit challenges the lower court's decision.
He gets angry if anyone challenges his religious beliefs.
Challenges to fight are punishable by fine and imprisonment.
Horace challenges superiority above all the poets.
Those students are not equipped for the challenges of college.
The company is ready to meet the challenges of the next few years.
The person at the headship of the firm will face daunting challenges, given the current state of the economy.
